@{B}·@{UB} Preface @{I}TCalcStats @{UI}v2.0b.
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 What is it?! In brief... tools for number crunching!

 The included ARexx scripts will allow you to perform a comprehensive range
 of statistical analysis tests on raw sample data. The statistical approach
 and the workings of all these scripts are extensively explained in this 
 AmigaGuide and the associated HTML documentation. In effect, little prior
 knowledge of statistical analysis is assumed for application of many of the
 test procedures. This package is aimed at:

 - Scientists researching in physical, biological and social sciences, etc.

 - Students who are likely to need to conduct statistical analysis as part
   of their studies.

 - Market researchers and anyone else who wants to analyze trends in sample
   data.


 Although several statistical analysis programs exist for the Amiga
 platform this suite of ARexx scripts have been designed to provide an
 extensive range of @{"summary statistics" LINK TOOLSLIST 12}, @{"parametric" LINK TOOLSLIST 27} and additional
 @{"non-parametric" LINK TOOLSLIST 97} tests of hypotheses for a variety of data sources.

 **********************************************************************
 *      							      *
 *  This package is a series of analysis tools designed for use with  *
 *  @{"TurboCalc v5.x" LINK TURBOCALC} by Michael Friedrich.    			 *
 *      							      *
 **********************************************************************

 A similar set of tools are available for Microsoft Excel on the PC and Mac
 in the form of 'add-ins' but this package is intended to perform beyond
 these existing capabilities. It contains numerous extra features:

 - Greater support for @{"non-parametric" LINK TOOLSLIST 97} tests such as:

   - Test for normality in data distributions.

   - Mann-Whitney test.

   - Wilcoxon paired sample or signed rank test.

   - Kruskal-Wallis test.

   - Friedman rank test... @{B}Etc@{UB}.

 - Support for unusual or specialised tests:

   - Shannon-Wiener biodiversity index test.

 - Enhanced output. Results include probability and critical value figures
   for both one-tailed and two-tailed tests at both 0.05 and 0.01 levels of
   significance, where applicable.

@ENDNODE

