@{B}· @{UB}Details of the statistical analysis tools:
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 This section contains details of specific use and workings of the
 statistical tools included in this package. All worked examples found in
 sections below and the scripts themselves will assume (where necessary)
 that statistical tests are conducted at the 0.05 or 0.01 level of
 probability or significance. Most of the information found in these
 sections will assume some prior knowledge of statistical analysis theory
 and application. If required, click @{"here" LINK STATANALYSIS} for further information.
 You may also want to pursue further @{"references" LINK REFS} for information
 beyond the scope of this document.


 @{FG SHINE}Descriptive or summary statistics@{FG TEXT}

  Test: @{B}Descriptive statistics for sample data@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK DESCSTATS}.
  Script: Descriptive_Stats.rexx

  Test: @{B}Frequency distribution histogram@{UB}.
  Tool: for description and operation select @{"here" LINK HISTOGRAM}.
  Script: Histogram.rexx

  Test: @{B}Relative rank and percentile calculation@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK RANK&PERCENT}.
  Script: Rank&Percentile.rexx


 @{FG SHINE}Parametric statistical tests@{FG TEXT}

  Test: @{B}T-test of two independent sample means@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK TTEST1}.
  Script: T-test_IndSamples.rexx

  Test: @{B}T-test of two independent means-with unequal variances@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK TTEST2}.
  Script: T-test_IndSamples_UneqVar.rexx

  Test: @{B}T-test of two paired or correlated sample means@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK TTEST3}.
  Script: T-test_Corr_Sample.rexx

  Test: @{B}F-ratio test for homogeneity of sample variances@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK FRATIO}.
  Script: F_Ratio.rexx

  Test: @{B}One-way analysis of variance@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK ANOVA1}.
  Script: anova_oneway.rexx

  Test: @{B}Two-way analysis of variance@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK ANOVA2}.
  Script: ANOVA_TwoWay.rexx

  Test: @{B}Two-way analysis of variance without replication@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK ANOVA3}.
  Script: ANOVA_TWOWAY_NO_REP.rexx

  Test: @{B}Pearson's product moment correlation between two variables@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK CORRELATION1}.
  Script: Correlation.rexx


 @{FG SHINE}Non-parametric statistical tests@{FG TEXT}

  Test: @{B}Mann-Whitney U-test@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK MANNWHITNEY1}.
  Script: Mann-Whitney.rexx

  Test: @{B}Smirnov Test on Two Independent Samples@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK SMIRNOV}.
  Script: Smirnov_2W.rexx

  Test: @{B}Cochrans Test for Related Observations@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK COCHRAN}.
  Script: Cochran.rexx

  Test: @{B}Wilcoxon paired sample or sign rank test@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK WILCOXON}.
  Script: Wilcoxon_Sign_Rank.rexx

  Test: @{B}Kruskal-Wallis H test@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK KRUSWALL}.
  Script: Kruskal-Wallis.rexx

  Test: @{B}Chi-square (x˛) sign test of two independent samples@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK CHISQUARE1}.
  Script: Chi-Sq_2_Ind_Sam.rexx

  Test: @{B}Chi-square (x˛) test for independence of sample data@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK HETEROGENEITY}.
  Script: Chi-Sq_Indep.rexx

  Test: @{B}Chi-square (x˛) goodness of fit test@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK GOODFIT}.
  Script: Chi-Sq_GO_Fit.rexx

  Test: @{B}"Normality" - Chi-square (x˛) GOF test for sample normal distribution@{UB}.
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK NORMALITY}.
  Script: Normality.rexx

  Test: @{B}Shapiro-Wilk test for normality@{UB}
  Tool: For description and operation select @{"here" LINK SHAPIRO}.
  Script: Shapiro.rexx

  Test: @{B}Fisher exact test@{UB}
